Before the passing on of Dr Likwelile, Tanzanians were already in mourning because just last week, the country lost its Chief Secretary, Ambassador John Kijazi. 

Ambassador Kijazi passed away in Dodoma at Benjamin Mkapa Hospital and was buried at his ancestral home in Korogwe District, Tanga Region. 






Former Bank of Tanzania Governor Prof Benno Ndulu dies aged 71
Photo credit: File | Nation Media Group

 

Zanzibar's Seif Hamad 

But that seemed to be just a continuation of the grief that had engulfed the country since the start of February. On February 17, the nation woke up to the sad news of the death of Zanzibar’s First Vice President and national chairman of the opposition party, ACT-Wazalendo, Seif Sharif Hamad, 77. 

He died at the Muhimbili National Hospital (MNH) where he had been admitted from February 9. 

The cause of Mr Hamad’s death was not immediately established but on January 31 he was reportedly hospitalised at Mnazi Mmoja Hospital in Zanzibar after allegedly testing positive for Covid-19. 



